<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Sharks up to five metres long have swarmed a popular NSW beach after a whale carcass washed up on the rocks leading to a mass feeding frenzy.</p>

<p>Bulli and Sandon Point beaches near Wollongong on the state's south coast were closed on Thursday afternoon due to 'multiple large shark sightings'.</p>

<p>A day later monster sharks were spotted across the coastline circling around boats as local fishermen watched on in horror. </p>

